# Three migration pathways offer different risk-return profiles
@type: comparison

@compare:
  header: Pathway | Timeline | Cost | Risk | Value Realization
  row: Lift & Shift | 12–18 months | Low | Low | 25% of potential — cost savings only
  row: Re-platform | 18–30 months | Medium | Medium | 60% of potential — efficiency + flexibility
  row: Re-architect | 24–48 months | High | High | 100% of potential — full competitive platform

@exhibit: Exhibit 2 — Migration Strategy Options
@source: McKinsey Cloud Migration Benchmark, 2024

@notes: Most clients default to lift-and-shift out of risk aversion. Replatforming is typically the correct risk-adjusted choice for the core application portfolio.

